vortex. The stable stratification created a\ngeneralised increment of pollutant within the canopy, with concentrations twice\nas large. Turbulent pollutant fluxes were found significant only at roof level\nand close to the source. On the other hand, in the windward wall-heated case\nthe reduction of the mean flux renders the turbulent component relevant in\nother locations as well.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Nov 2018 13:14:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 Jan 2019 18:11:45 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 4 Apr 2019 13:58:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-16"}
